## Dead ends / scope decisions (deliberately NOT done)
- Did NOT broaden detection to TransportServerError 401/403 or wandb.AuthenticationError.
  Rationale: per the in-code comment (and confirmed shape), gorilla returns PERMISSION_ERROR
  (a TransportQueryError) for BOTH "forbidden" and "not-logged-in", so both the no-access
  and invalid/absent-key cases already funnel through the existing _is_permission_denied
  check. Broadening would also drag in retry-semantics changes (_is_retryable_project_exception
  retries TransportServerError) and relies on unverifiable assumptions about whether the
  server returns HTTP 4xx vs 200-with-errors. Kept the change minimal and narrow.
- Did NOT create a weave/errors.py. The task referenced it but it does not exist; the
  established type for this boundary is UnableToCreateProjectError (added by #7373) in
  project_creator.py. Reused it. It is NOT re-exported at weave top level (users catch it
  via weave.wandb_interface.project_creator).

## Hints & warnings
- TRADEOFF (flag for reviewer): #7373 used `from None` intentionally to "suppress the raw
  gql traceback". The task explicitly asked for `from err`, so this commit reverses that:
  the gql TransportQueryError now shows above the friendly message on an uncaught error
  ("The above exception was the direct cause..."). The friendly UnableToCreateProjectError
  is still the LAST/most-prominent frame, and the cause is now available for debugging. If
  the team prefers the cleaner no-traceback UX, revert just the `from exception` -> `from None`
  and the test's __cause__ assertion.
- test_ensure_project_exists_authentication_error (line ~124) still asserts a raw
  AuthenticationError propagates — left as-is. AuthenticationError is a login-time error
  (weave.login in weave_init.py), a DIFFERENT boundary from ensure_project_exists; in the
  real ensure_project_exists path gql raises Transport* errors, not AuthenticationError.
- Assert on the WHOLE message string (repo rule: no substring/`in` checks). If you tweak
  the message wording, update the test's full == block.

